Package unaryPredicate Description

A unary predicate is an object that can test whether a value satisifes a given condition. For example, a given unary predicate might be able to test whether an integer is even. This package defines the unary predicate interfaces, and provides some examples of unary predicates.
Version:
September 2019
Author:
Hugh Osborne
